# Vision Plan

## Save on Vision Exams, Frames, and Contacts

Walmart's vision plan provides affordable eye care for associates and their families with low copays and comprehensive coverage.

---

## Key Features

### Coverage Highlights
- **Eye Exams**: $4 copay, once per calendar year.
- **Frames**: $130 frame allowance, once per calendar year.
- **Lenses**: $4 materials copay when purchased with frames.
- **Progressive Lenses**: Additional $45 copay.
- **Contact Lenses**: $130 allowance instead of glasses, once per calendar year.

### Flexible Provider Options
- Access care at Walmart Vision Centers, Sam's Club Optical, or any Vision Service Plan (VSP) network provider nationwide.
- Ensure your provider is in the VSP network before receiving services.

### ID Cards
- **With Walmart Medical Plan**: VSP contact details included on your plan ID card.
- **Without Medical Plan**: A separate VSP ID card will be mailed to your home.

---

## Using the Plan

1. Confirm your provider is a VSP network provider.
2. Inform the provider that you are a VSP member and present your ID card if applicable.
3. Pay your copay and any other required charges at the time of your visit.
4. If benefits are not automatically processed, file a claim at [Walmart VSP Portal](https://walmart.vspforme.com).

---

## Additional Resources

- **Find a VSP Provider**: [Locate Providers](https://www.vsp.com/eye-doctor?sortByPremier=true)
- **Order Contacts Online**:
  - [Walmart Contacts](https://www.walmartcontacts.com/)
  - [Sam’s Club Contacts](https://www.samsclubcontacts.com/)

# Hawaii Benefits

## Medical benefits tailored for Hawaii associates.

Walmart provides exclusive medical plans for associates in Hawaii with unique coverage and resources.

---

## Two Exclusive Medical Plans
1. **HMSA**:
   - Comprehensive care and services.
   - Dedicated to Hawaii residents.
   - Learn more at [HMSA.com](https://hmsa.com) or call [808-948-6372](tel:8089486372).

2. **Kaiser Hawaii**:
   - One of the nation’s leading HMOs.
   - Specializes in managed healthcare.
   - Learn more at [KaiserPermanente.org](https://healthy.kaiserpermanente.org/oregon-washington/front-door) or call [800-966-5955](tel:8009665955).

---

## Enrollment and Coverage Details

### When to Enroll:
- **Hourly and Temporary Associates**:
  - Enroll any time after your first pay period and before your effective date.
- **Management Associates**:
  - Must enroll before the 60th day of employment.
- **Annual Enrollment Period**:
  - Open to all eligible associates for changes or new sign-ups.
- **Election Change Events**:
  - Marriage, divorce, new child, or other significant life events allow for related changes.

### Coverage Start Dates:
- **Management Associates**:
  - Coverage begins on the hire date.
- **Hourly and Temporary Associates**:
  - Starts after 20+ hours/week for four consecutive weeks or on the 89th day of continuous employment.

---

## Cost and Additional Information
- **Plan Costs**:
  - View per-pay-period costs at [Compare Plans](http://one.walmart.com/ComparePlans).
- **Other Benefits**:
  - Aligns with mainland associate options, except for disability benefits for full-time hourly associates.

# PPO Plan by Aetna

## Flexible Coverage with Low Costs

The PPO Plan offers extensive coverage for associates and their families with predictable costs and a wide provider network.

---

## Key Features

### Low Copays
- $15 for primary care visits.
- $25 for specialists.
- $25 for behavioral health visits.
- $50 for urgent care and emergency services.

### Low Deductibles
- $300 for individual coverage.
- $600 for associates with dependents.

### Extensive Coverage
- Up to 90% coverage for in-network eligible expenses after meeting the deductible.
- Includes additional benefits like acupuncture, chiropractic care, and vision care.

---

## Plan Highlights

### Preventive Care
- 100% coverage for in-network preventive care, including annual checkups, vaccinations, and mammograms.

### Affordable Prescriptions
- Generic drugs: $10.
- Brand-name drugs: $30.
- Specialty drugs: $30.

### Out-of-Pocket Maximums
- $1,500 for individual coverage.
- $3,000 for family coverage.
- Once reached, all eligible in-network expenses are covered at 100% for the remainder of the year.

---

## Enrollment and Eligibility

### Current Status
- Enrollment is closed for new participants.
- Associates and family members already enrolled can continue with the plan until 2026.

### Who's Eligible?
- Designed for U.S.-based Global Tech associates working in select areas.

- Personalized treatment plans and ongoing guidance.

### Cost-Free for Most Plans
- $0 copay with Premier, Contribution, and Local Plans.
- Saver Plan participants must meet their deductible first.

### Convenient Access
- Save time and money by skipping in-person visits.
- Perform therapy exercises anytime, anywhere through your smartphone or tablet.

---

## How Virtual Physical Therapy Helps
- Prevent and heal muscle and joint pain.
- Tune your body to move better.
- Manage chronic conditions with personalized techniques.
- Prevent injuries with self-directed programs tailored to your needs.
- Improve emotional health by addressing physical pain.

  - Saver

# 2025 Annual Enrollment FAQ

[What is Annual Enrollment?](#)

Annual Enrollment is a yearly event when all eligible associates can sign up for medical plans and other benefits, make changes to their current benefits, and explore many more tools and programs to help ​​​them ​live better.

[When is Annual Enrollment this year?](#)

Annual Enrollment starts Saturday, Oct. 12, 2024, and ends at 11:59 p.m. (Central Time) on Friday, Nov. 8, 2024.

[Where can I get more information?](#)

Go to your personalized Benefits Guide atOne.Walmart.com/AEstarting Oct. 12. You can learn what’s new for your location, see if your plans are changing next year, check the benefits you’re already enrolled in, and see everything else you can enroll in. Plus, you’ll find more tools for living better that don’t require enrollment.

[One.Walmart.com/AE](http://one.walmart.com/AE)

[How do I enroll?](#)

Once you’ve reviewed your Benefits Guide, just choose any of the ​​​gold ​“Enroll now” or “Click here to get started” ​buttons to go to Online Enrollment. You can also go straight toOne.Walmart.com/Enroll.

[One.Walmart.com/Enroll](http://one.walmart.com/Enroll)

[Is enrollment required?](#)

Annual Enrollment is optional for all associates. But if you’re in a location where your current medical plan will no longer be available in 2025, you should complete an enrollment session to make sure you get the medical plan you want.​ If you don’t make another choice, you’ll be enrolled in the Premier Plan at your current coverage tier (such as associate-only​​ or family​​). ​​​​​​​​​​To see if you’re in one of these areas, and to learn more about everything that’s available, see your personalized Benefits Guide atOne.Walmart.com/AE.Even if you’re not affected by a plan change, Annual Enrollment is still a great time to look at your current benefits, think about any changes you might want to make​, make sure your beneficiaries are up to date​,​ and learn about all the ways you can live better in 2025.

[One.Walmart.com/AE](http://one.walmart.com/AE)

[What's changing for 2025?](#)

Most areas won’t see any major changes for 2025. But there are some changes in limited areas, and we’re expanding some​ health care and mental health​​​​​ programs nationwide. You can see what affects you and learn more on your Benefits Guide atOne.Walmart.com/AE.

[One.Walmart.com/AE](http://one.walmart.com/AE)

[One.Walmart.com/QualityProviders](http://One.Walmart.com/QualityProviders)

[One.Walmart.com/OmadaHealth](https://bit.ly/25AEWebWebv4VirtualCare_lid204292)

[One.Walmart.com/AiRCare](https://bit.ly/25AEWebWebv3AirCare_lid204341)

[One.Walmart.com/ONEAtWorkSave.](http://one.walmart.com/AE)

​​​*One is a financial technology company, not a bank. Banking services provided by Coastal Community Bank, Member FDIC.​​

[​​Why are some HMO plans being discontinued?​​​](#)

​​We regularly review all our medical plan offerings regularly to make sure they’re meeting our high standards while delivering care at a cost that’s appropriate for Walmart and our associates. As a result of a recent review​, we’ve decided to​​​​ discontinue four Geisinger HMO plans for 2025​​.

[​​​If my HMO is discontinued, what are my options now?​​](#)

​​​The lineup of plans you can choose from depends on your work location. All areas have access to the Premier Plan, and some offer other plans as well. If you choose the Premier ​​​​Plan,​​ you’ll get simple copays for doctor visits like you do now​​,​​ ​​​​but it’ll cost you less ​than ​​what you pay​​ per ​​​​pay period ​​​​today​​.​​

[If my HMO is discontinued, w​​​​hat if I can’t decide​​ on a new medical plan​​?​​](#)

​​​If you don’t choose a new plan, or if you don’t complete an enrollment session, you’ll automatically be enrolled in the Premier Plan, our most popular option, at your current coverage tier (such as associate-only).​

[Will I have different providers if I’m in a discontinued HMO?](#)

The list of in-network doctors and other providers will change when you change plans. However, most providers are in-network in​ more than one network, and many of the providers in your Geisinger plan are also in-network for our national plans like the Premier Plan. You can see the providers in your ​new network atIncludedHealth.com/Walmart.

[IncludedHealth.com/Walmart](http://includedhealth.com/Walmart)

[​​​Why are some areas switching third-party​​ administrators?​​](#)

Walmart works with three major ​​​​​third-party​​ administrators ​​​​—​​​​Blue Advantage​​ Administrators of Arkansas​​, Aetna, and UMR​​—​​​​ to help us ​​administer​​​​ our national medical plans like the Premier Plan. A key role of​ these administrators is maintaining networks of doctors and other ​providers at a competitive cost. We review and analyze these networks regularly to ​​​​make sure ​​we’re providing access to enough providers across all specialties so our associates have a choice of ​​​​​​​​providers ​​at a competitive cost​​, no matter where they live and work. ​

[Can I keep my third-party administrator if I switch ​​medical ​​plans?​​](#)

​​​Not if you switch among the Premier, Contribution, and Saver plans. Each facility has a single administrator assigned to it for all these plans. ​​​​So,​​ if the administrator in your area is changing there’s no way to keep your current one. However, if you have an HMO plan available where you work, that plan will have a different administrator and a different network of providers.​​​​​​​​

[​​​Will I have different providers if my third-party administrator changes?​​](#)

​​​The list of in-network doctors and other providers may​​ change ​​​​if ​​your administrator does. However, most providers are in-network i​n more than one network, and many of the ​​​​providers​​ in your current network ​​​​may ​​also be in the new one. You can see who’s in your new network atIncludedHealth.com/Walmart.​​

[IncludedHealth.com/Walmart](http://includedhealth.com/Walmart)

[Compare ​Plans​​ shows the PPO Plan is available in my facility. Why can’t I enroll?​​](#)

​​​The PPO Plan has been closed to new enrollment​​ and is only available to associates who have previously enrolled in the plan​​. ​​​​Because our systems ​​​​show plans that are available​​ at the facility level, not for each individual, ​​​​Compare Plans​​​​ still shows that plan as available for your location.​​

[Why is the PPO Plan closed to new enrollment?](#)

​​​Our ​​b​​​​enefits team regularly reviews the plans and programs we offer to ​​​​make sure​​ associates have equitable access to ​​plans that ​​support their health and well-being. As a result of one of these reviews, we determined that the PPO medical plan option would ​​no longer be available ​​​​to new participants, and there will be no exceptions to this decision. ​​

[​​​Why is the PPO Plan sunsetting as of Jan. 1, 2026? ​​](#)

​​​Providingallassociates equitable access to medical plans that support their health and well-being is a part of Walmart’s mission to help associates save money and live better. By sunsetting the PPO Plan, associates will have the same Walmart medical plan options offered nationwide.​​

[What happens if i’m already in the PPO Plan?](#)

​​Right now, nothing. You’ll keep your plan with no changes through 2025 as long as you remain at the same location. However, ​the plan will be discontinued ​​​on Jan. 1, 2026. Annual Enrollment is a good opportunity to look ahead and check out your other medical plan options.

[What if I’m in the PPO Plan and I move to another location?](#)

​​​If you currently are in the PPO Plan, you can keep it if you transfer to another facility that also has the PPO Plan available. If you move to a facility that doesn’t offer the PPO ​​​​Plan,​​ you’ll have to choose a new plan from the options available there.​​

[What's happening with ​medical plan costs?](#)

We're holding cost increases to a minimum again for 2025. ​​Medical plan costs will go up for both Walmart and associates. ​​​​​Your cost for dental and vision coverage will stay the same, and your cost for optional short-term disability coverage will go down. Go toOne.Walmart.com/AEto see how your plan’s costs are changing and to compare your options.

# Dental Plan

## A whole new reason to smile.

Get affordable dental care for your whole family, from checkups to major work—including orthodontia treatment.

---

### Smart Coverage for You and Your Family

#### 100% Preventive Care
- Regular cleanings, X-rays, and exams are fully covered with Delta Dental PPO dentists.
- 80% coverage when using Delta Dental Premier dentists for preventive services.

#### Fillings and More
- 80% coverage for most regular care, including fillings and non-surgical periodontics.
- 50% coverage for major work like crowns and oral surgery.

#### Braces, Too
- $1,500 orthodontia coverage after one year of enrollment.

---

## How It Works
- Preventive care requires no deductible:
  - $75 deductible for individuals and $225 for families for other services.
- Plan covers:
  - **80% for basic care** (e.g., root canals, fillings).
  - **50% for major care** (e.g., implants, dentures).

---

## Plan Details and Limits
- **Annual Deductible:** $75 per individual, $225 per family.
- **Annual Maximum Benefit:** $2,500 per person.
- **Enrollment Requirement:** Must remain enrolled for two calendar years.

---

### Using the Plan
1. Choose any Delta Dental PPO or Premier dentist.
2. Show your ID card at your visit.
3. Pay charges during your visit, if applicable.

---

## Orthodontia Details
- Eligible after one year of enrollment.
- $1,500 lifetime maximum coverage per person.
- No deductible for orthodontia charges.
